HEADWORD: Poultry
<hw>Poul"try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Poult</er>.]</ety> <def>Domestic fowls reared for the table, or for
their eggs or feathers, such as cocks and hens, capons, turkeys, ducks,
and geese.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

